  "prompt": "Why did Paul Manafort quit as Donald Trump's presidential campaign chairman?",
  "response": "Paul Manafort resigned as Donald Trump's presidential campaign chairman on August 19, 2016. His resignation came amid increasing scrutiny over his past work for pro-Russian politicians in Ukraine and mounting allegations of impropriety. News reports had surfaced detailing his involvement in undisclosed lobbying efforts, and questions were raised about his business dealings and financial transactions. The controversies surrounding Manafort were seen as a distraction and potentially damaging to Trump's campaign, leading to his departure from the position.",
